nce >= 0.8\n\nOutput your evaluation as JSON matching the NetworkEvaluation schema.\n", "user_message": "Evaluate this synthesis network:\n\nTARGET MOLECULE: Glycine\nOVERALL STRATEGY: This network models glycine as the convergence product of ten literature-grounded prebiotic routes centered on the major hubs HCN, formaldehyde, aminoacetonitrile, glyoxylate, and glycine. Hydrothermal chemistry supplies reduced carbon intermediates from CO2/H2 on iron-sulfur and metal oxide minerals, surface environments generate and concentrate HCN and aldehydes and drive Strecker, Bucherer-Bergs, HCN polymer, cyanosulfidic, UV-photochemical, and freezing-enabled pathways, and biochemical/prebiotic settings hydrolyze, exchange, and oligomerize products. The design follows the provided literature by using Strecker chemistry as the dominant route, Bucherer-Bergs as a CO2-assisted branch, hydrothermal reductive amination through glyoxylate on ferroan brucite or ZnS-like photochemical amination analogs, and Fischer-Tropsch-type chemistry only as an upstream source of HCN/formaldehyde rather than a direct one-step route to glycine.\n\nMOLECULES (27 nodes):\n  - mol_001: CO2 (carbon dioxide) [starting]\n  - mol_002: H2 (hydrogen) [starting]\n  - mol_003: NH3 (ammonia) [starting]\n  - mol_004: HCN (hydrogen cyanide) [hub_intermediate]\n  - mol_005: CH2O (formaldehyde) [hub_intermediate]\n  - mol_006: CH3NO (formamide) [intermediate]\n  - mol_007: C2H3NO (glycolonitrile) [hub_intermediate]\n  - mol_008: CH3NO (aminomethanol) [intermediate]\n  - mol_009: CH3N (methanimine) [intermediate]\n  - mol_010: C2H4N2 (aminoacetonitrile) [hub_intermediate]\n  - mol_011: C2H4N2O (glycinamide) [intermediate]\n  - mol_012: C2H5NO2 (glycine) [target]\n  - mol_013: C2H2N4 (DAMN) [intermediate]\n  - mol_014: HCNO (cyanate/isocyanate pool) [intermediate]\n  - mol_015: C3H4N2O2 (hydantoin) [intermediate]\n  - mol_016: C3H6N2O3 (N-carbamoylglycine) [intermediate]\n  - mol_017: CHO3- (glyoxylate) [hub_intermedi