d as speculative or minor.']\n\n============================================================\nAddress the above issues in your new network. Do NOT repeat the same mistakes.\n", "raw_response": "{\n  \"target_molecule\": \"Glycine\",\n  \"overall_strategy\": \"This network targets glycine through ten literature-grounded, convergent prebiotic routes centered on five hubs: hydrogen cyanide, formaldehyde, aminoacetonitrile, glyoxylate, and glycine itself. Hydrothermal chemistry supplies reduced C1-C3 feedstocks such as formate, formaldehyde, and pyruvate from CO2/H2 on Fe-S and Fe-oxide minerals under alkaline serpentinizing conditions. Surface environments generate and concentrate HCN, drive Strecker chemistry, Bucherer-Bergs diversion, cyanosulfidic photoredox chemistry, and HCN polymer hydrolysis under wet-dry, UV, and eutectic concentration regimes. Biochemical/prebiotic settings complete slower hydrolyses, transductions, and oligomerization. The ten pathways are not isolated; they share intermediates and environmental transfer, with hydrothermal products feeding surface reactions and surface nitrile products feeding biochemical hydrolysis to glycine.\",\n  \"molecules\": [\n    {\n      \"id\": \"mol_001\",\n      \"formula\": \"CO2\",\n      \"iupac_name\": \"carbon dioxide\",\n      \"common_name\": \"carbon dioxide\",\n      \"inchi\": \"InChI=1S/CO2/c2-1-3\",\n      \"role\": \"starting\",\n      \"environment_formed\": null\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"mol_002\",\n      \"formula\": \"H2\",\n      \"iupac_name\": \"molecular hydrogen\",\n      \"common_name\": \"hydrogen\",\n      \"inchi\": \"InChI=1S/H2/h1H\",\n      \"role\": \"starting\",\n      \"environment_formed\": null\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"mol_003\",\n      \"formula\": \"NH3\",\n      \"iupac_name\": \"azane\",\n      \"common_name\": \"ammonia\",\n      \"inchi\": \"InChI=1S/H3N/h1H3\",\n      \"role\": \"starting\",\n      \"environment_formed\": null\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"m